title: The Complete Artie Shaw Vol. 1 (1938-39) Bluebird 24/96 vinyl
description:
THE COMPLETE ARTIE SHAW, VOLUME ONE 1938-1939

24/96 MONO VINYL RIP with SCANS

SIDE A:
1. Begin The Beguine
2. Indian Love Call (vocal by Tony Pastor)
3. Comin' On
4. Any Old Time (vocal by Billie Holiday)
5. I Can't Believe That You're In Love With Me

Chuck Peterson, Claude Bowen, John Best (tp), George Arus, Ted Vesely, Harry Rodgers (tb), Artie Shaw (cl), Les Robinson, Hank Freeman (cl, as), Tony Pastor (cl, ts, vcl), Ronnie Perry (cl, ts), Les Burness (p), Al Avola (g), Sid Weiss (b), Cliff Leeman (d); NYC, July 24, 1938

6. Nightmare
7. Non-Stop Flight

SIDE B:
1. Yesterdays
2. What Is This Thing Called Love
3. You're A Sweet Little Headache (vocal by Helen Forrest)
4. I Have Eyes (vocal by Helen Forrest)

Chuck Peterson, Claude Bowen, John Best (tp), George Arus, Russell Brown, Harry Rodgers (tb), Artie Shaw (cl), George Koenig, Hank Freeman (cl, as), Tony Pastor (cl, ts, vcl), Ronnie Perry (cl, ts), Les Burness (p), Al Avola (g), Sid Weiss (b), Cliff Leeman (d);
NYC, September 27, 1938

5. Between A Kiss And A Sigh (vocal by Helen Forrest)
6. Thanks For Ev'rything (vocal by Helen Forrest)
7. Deep In A Dream (vocal by Helen Forrest)
8. Day After Day (vocal by Helen Forrest)

SIDE C:
1. Softly, As In A Morning Sunrise
2. Copenhagen

Same as above except Les Robinson (as) replaces Koenig; NYC, November 17, 1938

3. A Room With A View (vocal by Helen Forrest)
4. Say It With A Kiss (vocal by Helen Forrest)
5. They Say (vocal by Helen Forrest)
6. It Took A Million Years (vocal by Helen Forrest)
7. Jungle Drums
8. It Had To Be You

Chuck Peterson, Bernie Privin, John Best (tp), George Arus, Harry Rodgers, Les Jenkins (tb), Artie Shaw (cl), Les Robinson, Hank Freeman (as), Tony Pastor (ts, vcl), Georgie Auld (ts), Bob Kitsis (p), Al Avola (g), Sid Weiss (b), George Wettling (d); NYC, December 19, 1938

9. Lover Come Back To Me

SIDE D:
1. My Heart Stood Still
2. Rosalie
3. Supper Time (vocal by Helen Forrest)
4. Vilia

Same as above except Buddy Rich (d) replaces Wettling.; NYC, January 17, 1939

5. The Man I Love
6. The Donkey Serenade
7. Bill (vocal by Helen Forrest)
8. Zigeuner
9. Carioca

Same as above; NYC, January 23, 1939

1976 Bluebird/RCA
